<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FCFFE4148A75473FE2BFAF4" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FCFFE4148A75473FD19FB2F" blockId="385.[151,1437,863,1392]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FCFFE4148A75473FE09FC88" bold="true" box="[151,428,863,888]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 6.0 mm. Yellow-ferruginous, except petiole black. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 9:8:40:32:25:17:11:8:7:10. Head excavated, shiny, unsculptured, except occiput and anterior region of face granulated; frontal line incomplete, absent near clypeus; occipital carina incomplete, shortly present on sides of posterior ocelli; POL = 6; OL = 6; OOL = 27. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum shiny, hairless, granulated, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum granulated, with two lateral pointed protrusions. Scutellum shiny, distinct. Metanotum transversely striate, not hollow behind scutellum, with sides not protruding. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, with disc, anterior and posterior surface transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete, very thin. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 57:8:17:75:104. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCFFE414C315353FBDAFB67" box="[1025,1151,1151,1175]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Plate 120A</figureCitation>
) with one large subdistal tooth and one row of eight lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCFFE414B745388FC67FB4C" box="[836,962,1188,1212]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Plate 120A</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 19 + 22 lamellae; distal apex with at least 30 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FCFFE4148F753C0FE2BFAF4" blockId="385.[151,1437,863,1392]" box="[199,398,1260,1284]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">
